.237-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to protect employees from certain automatic deductions or transfers for the purpose of funding political contributions. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. No person may consent to any automatic payroll deduction or authorize any automatic periodic checking account transfer for the purposes of enabling the recipient to make political contributions to any candidates or causes unless: (1) The consent or authorization is voluntary; (2) The consent or authorization is entered into prior to any deduction; (3) Each individual consent or authorization is supported by a separate consent or authorization form prescribed by the State Board of Elections. Each consent or authorization form shall be renewed at least annually or the consent or authorization is subject to expiration at the end of twelve months and becomes void. Section 2. Any political contribution from any person to a recipient shall be remitted separately from contributions for dues, fees, or the payments to the recipient. 170 copies were printed on recycled paper by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.093 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from existing statutes are indicated by overstrikes."}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 4313, "action_date": "2013-01-28T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 24817, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/24817.pdf", "status_text": "First read in House and referred to", "journal_page": 215, "committee_id_action": 202, "committee_id_assigned": 188, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 4313, "action_date": "2013-02-15T10:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 25645, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/25645.pdf", "status_text": "Scheduled for hearing", "journal_page": 0, "committee_id_action": 188, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "N